      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "One might ask if the expression Eq. (2.5) for the magnetic field could also get stringy or M-theoretic corrections, which while preserving its cohomology class, nevertheless modify Eq. (6.1). This is not possible because, as also shown in [CITATION_1] , the degeneracy of the lowest Landau level for the Hamiltonian Eq. (4.5) requires the gauge connection to satisfy the hermitian Yang-Mills equation, which for a U (1) gauge field implies Eq. (2.5)."
